      <h1 class='title'>Matters to which the court is to have regard on application under paragraph 26(1)(b)</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c281GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_281gc' title='Col. 281GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c281GC' name='column_281gc' href='#column_281gc' rel='bookmark'>281GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03690'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_301' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        31 (1) This paragraph applies if an application under paragraph 26 is made on the ground mentioned in paragraph 26(1)(b).
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03691'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_302' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) In deciding&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) whether the respondent has failed to provide, or to make a proper contribution towards, reasonable maintenance for the child of the family to whom the application relates, and</li>
        <li>(b) what order, if any, to make under this Part in favour of the child, the court must have regard to all the circumstances of the case.</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03692'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_303' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (3) Those circumstances include&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) the matters mentioned in paragraph 17(2)(a) to (e), and</li>
        <li>(b) if the child of the family to whom the application relates is not the child of the respondent, the matters mentioned in paragraph 17(3).</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03693'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_304' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (4) Paragraph 16(2)(c) (as it applies by virtue of paragraph 17(2)(e)) has effect as if for the reference in it to the breakdown of the civil partnership there were substituted a reference to&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) the failure to provide, or</li>
        <li>(b) the failure to make a proper contribution towards, reasonable maintenance for the child of the family to whom the application relates.</li></ol>
      </p>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
